{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThe epic needs a project-owned Pass 1 finder that rejects concrete portability failures without demanding generic portability prose. The fresh-worktree experiment has already proven that the project overlay, prompt loader, and production fan-in mechanism support this extension shape.\n\n## What\n\nAdd and activate `project.portability` in the project criteria overlay, author its Pass 1 rubric prompt, and add focused integration tests for prompt resolution, scope routing, and production finding fan-in.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`\n- `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md`\n- `tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py`\n- Pass 1 discovery for both leaf and container tickets\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Pass 2 validity or impact logic\n- Pass 3 disposition logic\n- coaching moves\n- live semantic calibration\n- remediation of existing portability debt\n\n## Approach\n\nUse the existing project overlay seam rather than adding a built-in criterion. This keeps rebar-specific policy in the rebar repository while exercising the same supported extension boundary available to clients. Configure `exec: 1-TURN`, `facet: project-invariants` (the established free-form project grouping used by `tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py`), `applies_at.scope: [container, leaf]`, `default_posture: blocking`, and `block_threshold: 0.9`, then add the id to `activate`.\n\nThe prompt front matter is fixed as:\n\n- `schema_version: 1`\n- `title: Rebar portability`\n- `description: Find concrete rebar portability failures across supported client shapes.`\n- `execution_mode: single_turn`, the prompt-library counterpart of routing `exec: 1-TURN`\n- `category: plan-review-criterion`\n- `dimension: project-invariants`\n\nThe rubric body uses these exact second-level headings so tests have a mechanical oracle:\n\n- `## Finding threshold`\n- `## Required finding fields`\n- `## Supported client-shape matrix`\n- `## Non-findings`\n\nUnder `Required finding fields`, specify `location: str` for the plan citation, `finding: str` for the assumption plus causal mechanism, `scenarios: list[str]` for the alternate client shape plus observable breakage, `evidence: list[str]` for the plan quote plus grounding facts, and `criteria: list[str]` containing `project.portability`. Under `Supported client-shape matrix`, require the literal labels `Harness`, `Target project`, `Platform and venue`, and `Project location and access`. Under `Non-findings`, require the literal rules `Silence about portability is not a finding` and `Project-specific behavior behind project configuration or an explicit extension boundary is allowed`.\n\n## Grounding\n\nPrior art is `tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py`, which proves the overlay and prompt contract, plus `tests/unit/workflow/test_production_batch_runner.py`, which covers the real fan-in runner. The parent epic `jira-reb-1003` records the completed experiment at `2026-07-16T00:50:08Z`: worktree `/Users/joeoakhart/rebar-jira-reb-1003-portability`, branch `experiment/jira-reb-1003-portability`, base `b0ac25447203d864463408c933497f21bc1f8dbf`, result `experiment=PASS; routed_scopes={container:true,leaf:true}; project_fan_in=[project.portability]; surfaced_findings=1; move_loaded=project-portability; restricted_to=project.portability`.\n\n## Test Strategy\n\nExercise the real overlay loader, prompt resolver, routing registry, and `ProductionBatchRunner` fan-in with deterministic fakes. Tests inspect the authored rubric contract; live LLM behavior belongs to the calibration child.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The overlay activates `project.portability` with `exec: 1-TURN`, `facet: project-invariants`, `applies_at.scope: [container, leaf]`, `default_posture: blocking`, and `block_threshold: 0.9`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k criterion_activation`.\n- [ ] The project rubric declares the exact six front-matter values specified in this plan. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k prompt_frontmatter`.\n- [ ] The project rubric resolves through the production prompt loader for `project.portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k prompt_resolution`.\n- [ ] A leaf plan routes `project.portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k leaf_routing`.\n- [ ] A container plan routes `project.portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k container_routing`.\n- [ ] Production project fan-in surfaces an injected `project.portability` finding. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k production_fan_in`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact `Required finding fields` heading plus the five typed field markers specified in this plan. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k finding_schema_markers`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact `Supported client-shape matrix` heading plus all four literal dimension labels. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k client_shape_matrix`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact rule `Silence about portability is not a finding`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k omission_guard`.\n- [ ] The rubric contains the exact rule allowing specialization behind project configuration or an explicit extension boundary. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k project_configuration_guard`.\n- [ ] Existing behavior remains unchanged when the project overlay is absent. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_criteria_overlay.py tests/unit/workflow/test_production_batch_runner.py`.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784164846062461001,"uuid":"2ba9f477-7dbf-4ac3-aa75-94f4f994687c"}